name: Paprika Chicken
author: Sue Primeau
summary: Chicken and paprika are considered an especially winning combination all over the world. This basic Paprika Chicken recipe is so easy, yet so good. Enjoy! Add chili powder or dried chives to the seasoning if desired.
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C)
Place chicken breasts side by side in baking dish
Sprinkle to taste with ground black pepper, garlic powder, poultry seasoning, and paprika
Bake in the preheated oven for 40 to 50 minutes, until chicken is no longer pink inside and the juices run clear
Check often and add a little water if the chicken starts to stick to the dish
